# Semantic Tokens — {{brand.name}}

> Role-based color bindings. **These are the only tokens component code may reference.**
> All semantic tokens have both a light (`:root`) and dark (`.dark`) value.

---

## Backgrounds

| Token | Light | Dark | Usage |
|---|---|---|---|
| `--color-bg-default` | `var(--gray-0)` | `var(--deep-950)` | Page background |
| `--color-bg-subtle` | `var(--gray-50)` | `var(--deep-900)` | Slightly elevated background (table rows, sidebar) |
| `--color-bg-ui` | `var(--gray-100)` | `var(--deep-800)` | UI surface (input backgrounds, card fills) |
| `--color-bg-brand` | `var(--primary-500)` | `var(--primary-500)` | Brand-filled CTA backgrounds |
| `--color-bg-brand-muted` | `var(--primary-50)` | `12% primary mix` | Subtle brand tint (tag backgrounds, active items) |

---

## Text

| Token | Light | Dark | Usage |
|---|---|---|---|
| `--color-text-primary` | `var(--deep-900)` | `var(--gray-50)` | Primary body text, headings |
| `--color-text-secondary` | `var(--gray-600)` | `var(--gray-400)` | Supporting text, metadata |
| `--color-text-muted` | `var(--gray-500)` | `var(--gray-500)` | Placeholder text, tertiary labels |
| `--color-text-disabled` | `var(--gray-400)` | `var(--gray-700)` | Disabled state labels |
| `--color-text-brand` | `var(--primary-700)` | `var(--primary-400)` | Brand-colored text, active nav items |
| `--color-text-on-brand` | `var(--gray-0)` | `var(--deep-950)` | Text on brand-colored backgrounds |

**Contrast requirements:**
- `--color-text-primary` on `--color-bg-default`: ≥ 7:1 (AAA)
- `--color-text-secondary` on `--color-bg-default`: ≥ 4.5:1 (AA)
- `--color-text-muted` on `--color-bg-default`: ≥ 4.5:1 (AA) — check both themes

